      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-05-07</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-05-27T21:34:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Soldiers Targeted by Offensive Profiteering Act of 2009 (STOP Act) - Prohibits any person, except with permission, from using the name or image of a protected individual in connection with any merchandise, retail product, impersonation, solicitation, or commercial activity in a manner calculated to connect the protected individual with that individual's service in the Armed Forces. Defines as a &quot;protected individual&quot; any person who: (1) is a member of the Armed Forces; or (2) was a member at any time after April 5, 1917, and, if not living, has a surviving spouse, child, parent, grandparent, or sibling.</p> <p>Authorizes the Attorney General to bring actions to enjoin violations of this Act. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
